	<digest>
		Build somax corpora from audio files
	</digest>

	<description>
		The somax.audiocorpusbuilder is used to construct a corpus from an audio file. A somax.player cannot read an audio file directly, it requires the audio to be analyzed and segmented before being able to parse it. The somax.audiocorpusbuilder does exactly that â€” it segments the audio file and analyzes it with regards to a number of descriptors and exports the result as a separate file, that then can be loaded into a somax.player.
	</description>

